rovides lightweight, throwaway instances of databases, web browsers, and other services running in Docker containers. It helps integration tests run against real dependencies instead of mocks or in-memory substitutes.\",\nmetadata/com.ethlo.time/itu/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/ethlo/time/itu/$version$/itu-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/com.ethlo.time/itu/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/ethlo/itu\",\nmetadata/com.ethlo.time/itu/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/ethlo/itu/tree/v$version$/src/test\",\nmetadata/com.ethlo.time/itu/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://javadoc.io/doc/com.ethlo.time/itu/$version$/\",\nmetadata/com.typesafe/config/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Typesafe Config is a JVM configuration library for loading and merging settings from Java properties, JSON, and HOCON files. It provides immutable Config objects, classpath and URL/file loading, substitutions, includes, and type conversions for application and library configuration.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.commons/commons-text/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Apache Commons Text provides reusable utilities and algorithms for processing and manipulating strings. It includes features such as string escaping, variable substitution, similarity and distance calculations, and text translation.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-interpolation/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Interpolation is a Java utility library for resolving and substituting expression placeholders in strings from pluggable value sources such as maps, properties, objects, and environment variables. It provides interpolator implementations, recursion handling, prefix-aware lookups, and reflection-based value extraction for tools that need Maven or Plexus-style configuration interpolation.\",\n./gradlew:231:# but POSIX shell has neither arrays nor command substitution, so instead we\nmetadata/oro/oro/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jakarta ORO is a Java text-processing library that provides Perl5-compatible regular expressions, AWK-like regular expressions, glob expressions, and utilities for substitutions, splits, and filename filtering. It is the Apache Jakarta successor to the OROMatcher, AwkTools, PerlTools, and TextTools libraries originally from ORO, Inc.\",\nmetadata/org.yaml/snakeyaml/2.0/reachability-metadata.json:5:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.yaml.snakeyaml.introspector.PropertySubstitute\"\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:33:- **HC-2 No library patching.** No substitutions, bytecode rewrites, or shaded forks of upstream libraries. Patching ships a different version than the one the user resolved through Maven Central, is invisible at the dependency-resolution layer, and is unstable across upstream releases.\n./forge/utility_scripts/strategy_loader.py:29:    \"\"\"Load a prompt template file and substitute placeholders.\"\"\"\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:246:| `strategy_loader` | Load named entries from `predefined_strategies.json` and substitute prompt template variables. |\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:100:  with the same substitution context as workflow prompts.\n./forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:107:- **Prompt rendering**: `_load_prompt` / `_render_prompt` substitute base\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:36:  repo. Test class naming substitutes `$<digit>` with `Anonymous<digit>` and\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:378:For different prompt behavior, create new prompt template files under `prompt_templates/` and reference them in the new strategy entry. Ensure that the context given to strategy workflows has prompt template placeholders. Prompt templates support Python string formatting with context variables (e.g., `{library}`, `{new_version}`) that are substituted at run time from the workflow context. Be sure that the workflow context contains placeholder keys.\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:60:            